Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
add_pg_cover_cell(25.10)                              add_pg_cover_cell(25.10)

Name
       add_pg_cover_cell  -  Adds instances of the PG cover cell at the speci-
       fied location or area, including the macro placement area by default

Syntax
       add_pg_cover_cell

        [-help]

       -cell <cellname>

       -inst_prefix <string>

       [{-location {<x y>} | -area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}}]

       [-area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>} [-exclude_macro_placement_area ]]

       Adds instances of the PG cover cell at the specified location or  area,
       including the macro placement area by default.

       Note:

              * The orientation of all added instances is R0.

              * In  order to make the PG cover cell instances exactly abutted,
                you must first set the block  snapping  rule  to  user-defined
                grid.  The  user-defined grid is defined using the core origin
                location and the PG cover cell size.

                setFPlanMode  -user_define_grid   {coreBox_llx,   coreBox_lly,
                cellBox_sizex, cellBox_sizey}

                setFPlanMode -snapBlockGrid userDefine

Parameters
       -area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Specifies  the coordinates of the area (<x1 y1 x2 y2>) where the
              instances of the PG cover cell will be added.

              Note:

              * All PG cover cell instances are placed abutted from {x1 y1}.

              * The -area and -location parameters are mutually exclusive.

              * All PG cover cell instances cover the whole specified area in-
                cluding the macro placement area by default.

              For example:

              add_pg_cover_cell -cell  <cellname>  -inst_prefix  pg_cover_cell
              -location {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}

              Data_type: box, optional

       -cell <cellname>
              Specifies the name of the PG cover cell.

              Data_type: string, required

       -exclude_macro_placement_area
              When  specified,  the  PG cover instances are placed only in the
              area specified using the -area parameter but excluding the  area
              where macros are placed.

              Note:  The  -exclude_macro_placement_area  parameter can only be
              used when the -area parameter is specified.

              Note: All PG cover cell instances cover the whole specified area
              including the macro placement area by default.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for  each add_pg_cover_cell parameter. For a detailed
              description of the command and all of its  parameters,  use  the
              man command:

              man add_pg_cover_cell

       -inst_prefix <prefix>
              Specifies a custom prefix for the added PG cover cell instances.

              Note:  The names of the added PG cover instances use the follow-
              ing format <<prefix>>_<<integer>>. For example, pg_cover_cell_1,
              pg_cover_cell_2, pg_cover_cell_3...

              Data_type: string, required

       -location {<x y>}
              Specifies the coordinates of the location (<x y>) where a single
              instance of the PG cover cell will be added.

              For example:

              add_pg_cover_cell -cell  <cellname>  -inst_prefix  pg_cover_cell
              -location {x y}

              Data_type: point, optional

Example
              *

                The following command adds instances of the PG cover cell at a
                specified area and excludes the macro placement area:

                add_pg_cover_cell  -cell  AA  -inst_prefix PGCC -area {150 150
                200 200} -exclude_macro_placement_area

